==Etymology==
From the French adjective, ''colique'', which referred to the lower part of the intestinal cavity.
Prior to that it comes from the Latin, ''coliculus'' and earlier from Greek, kolik-os with the same meaning.

==Noun==
#A term for severe pains which grip the abdomen or the disease that causes such pains (due to intestinal or bowel related problems).
#A medicinal plant used to relieve one of such symptoms.

